.TH "nfs4_update_server" 9 "nfs4_update_server" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfs4_update_server \- Move an nfs_server to a different nfs_client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nfs4_update_server
.BI "(struct nfs_server *server "  ","
.BI "const char *hostname "  ","
.BI "struct sockaddr *sap "  ","
.BI "size_t salen "  ","
.BI "struct net *net "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "server" 12
represents FSID to be moved
.IP "hostname" 12
new end-point's hostname
.IP "sap" 12
new end-point's socket address
.IP "salen" 12
size of "sap"
.IP "net" 12
net namespace
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The nfs_server must be quiescent before this function is invoked.
Either its session is drained (NFSv4.1+), or its transport is
plugged and drained (NFSv4.0).

Returns zero on success, or a negative errno value.
